TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RouteData

            displayed and the parameter values that will be supplied to the page.
            </summary>

            and accept a parameter named <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.LayoutComponentBase.Body" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsVirtualizationEnabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether the ui will be virtualized. Default <c>true</c>.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            To improve loading performance and network bandwidth usage, the cells are rendered as the user scrolls the controls. 
            If the number of cells is small it could be convenient to disable virtualization to improve scrolling speed.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Represents a grid column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Header
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets text shown in the header of this column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the format applied to the displayed data.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value indicating whether this column is read only. 
            If the grid is set to be read-only this property will be ignored.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsVisible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value indicating whether the column is visible and not collapsed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Binding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the binding.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowSorting
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the user can sort this column by tapping the column header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowFiltering
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the user can filter by this column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowGrouping
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the user can group by this column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SortMemberPath
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the path used to sort when the column header of this column is tapped.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            If no <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.SortMemberPath" /> is specified, the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.Binding" /> property will be used.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: FilterMemberPath
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the path used to filter this column.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            If no <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.FilterMemberPath" /> is specified, the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.Binding" /> property will be used.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: GroupMemberPath
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the path used to group this column.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            If no <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.GroupMemberPath" /> is specified, the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.Binding" /> property will be used.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the minimum width of the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the maximum width of the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the width of the column.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HorizontalAlignment
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the horizontal alignment.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderHorizontalAlignment
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the horizontal alignment of the header.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowMerging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that indicates whether cells in this column can be merged.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the type of keyboard shown when the cell is in edit-mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Aggregate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the type of aggregate to include in group headers.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueConverter
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets an <see cref="T:C1.Blazor.Core.IValueConverter" /> associated with this column's <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridColumn.Binding" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataMap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the DataMap used to convert raw values into display values for the column.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Columns with an associated <see cref="T:C1.Blazor.Grid.GridDataMap" /> will display a picker instead of the inline editor.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowResizing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value indicating whether this column can be resized.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowDragging
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value indicating whether this column can be dragged.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: WordWrap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value indicating whether cells in the column wrap their content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OptionsMenuVisibility
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the visibility of the options menu.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FilterLoading
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when the filter of a column is being loaded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OptionsLoading
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when the options of a column are being loaded.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

                <list type="bullet">

                <term>{name}</term>
                <description>The name of the property being grouped on.</description>
              </listheader>
              <item>
                <term>{value}</term>
                <description>The value of the property being grouped on.</description>
              </item>
              <item>
                <term>{level}</term>
                <description>The group level.</description>
              </item>
              <item>

If this event is not canceled, the edits will be committed or canceled depending on the setting of the CancelEdits property of the event argument.             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: GroupHeaderFormat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets or sets the format string used to create the group header content.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
                The string may contain any text, plus the following replacement strings: 
                <list type="bullet">
              <listheader>
                <term>{name}</term>
                <description>The name of the property being grouped on.</description>
              </listheader>
              <item>
                <term>{value}</term>
                <description>The value of the property being grouped on.</description>
              </item>
              <item>
                <term>{level}</term>
                <description>The group level.</description>
              </item>
              <item>
                <term>{count}</term>
                <description>The total number of items in this group.</description>
              </item>
            </list></remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The C1MaskedTextEditor control allows you to validate and format user input as it is entered, preventing users from entering invalid data.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mask
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets the input mask. The mask consists of a string that determines what class of character is acceptable at each input position. Valid mask characters are: 0 Digit (0-9) 9 Digit or space # Digit, space, or sign (+/-) L Letter ? Letter or space A Letter or digit a Letter, digit, or space & Any character . Localized decimal symbol , Localized thousand separator : Localized time separator / Localized date separator Other characters are treated as literals. They are displayed in the control but cannot be edited. For example, the mask "000-0000" causes the control to accept only digits at every position except the third, which always contains a dash.

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets or set the PromptChar value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Define the tab behavior if set.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnMaskFormatChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            /// Occurs when consistent content that conforms to the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox.MaskFormat" /> changes.
            Gets or sets the callback called when the MaskFormat is changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaskedTextChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Occurs when consistent content that conforms to the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox.Mask" /> changes in the text box.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Just after the Text property has beed changed via user input or code, 
            the <see cref="T:C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox" /> updates the text again in order to make it consistent with
            the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox.Mask" />. As a result, the TextChanged event can be triggered twice on each user
            input. In contrast to this, the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox.MaskedTextChanged" /> is triggered only when Text is
            updated with a value that conforms to the <see cref="P:C1.Blazor.Input.C1MaskedTextBox.Mask" />.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
